1
00:00:01,350 --> 00:00:07,000
If you cannot tell whether a market is an
uptrend or downtrend on whatever time frame

2
00:00:07,000 --> 00:00:12,490
you are looking at, you will almost certainly
get chopped up if you trade it.

3
00:00:12,490 --> 00:00:17,730
Many traders make the mistake of swing trading
in all market condition but sometimes the

4
00:00:17,730 --> 00:00:24,210
markets are too choppy and erratic to trade
with any accuracy or effectiveness.

5
00:00:24,210 --> 00:00:29,730
The number one rule of successful swing trading
is taking positions in the direction of a

6
00:00:29,730 --> 00:00:36,059
primary trend, but not anytime, only when
the markets are moving and are not consolidating.

7
00:00:36,059 --> 00:00:41,829
In this video, you’ll discover a reliable
indicator you must pay attention to, if you

8
00:00:41,829 --> 00:00:47,850
want to swing trade with the momentum on your
side and avoid consolidating markets.

9
