11
00:00:57,219 --> 00:01:01,670
So, I’ve mentioned earlier about choppy
markets.

12
00:01:01,670 --> 00:01:04,199
I’m sure you know them very well.

13
00:01:04,199 --> 00:01:09,600
You enter a swing trading position and the
price action becomes range bound, and is moving

14
00:01:09,600 --> 00:01:10,600
sideways.

15
00:01:10,600 --> 00:01:16,340
No profits and the market just go up and down
for days, around your entry point.

16
00:01:16,340 --> 00:01:22,780
The Fact is 80% of the Time the Market is
Choppy and your job, as a trader is to find

17
00:01:22,780 --> 00:01:26,890
ways to identify when the market is trending
or not.

18
00:01:26,890 --> 00:01:32,510
One of the easiest ways to identify whether
the market is moving or ranging is by using

19
00:01:32,510 --> 00:01:36,070
the Choppiness Index.

20
00:01:36,070 --> 00:01:40,860
Choppiness Index is based on chaos theory
and fractal geometry.

21
00:01:40,860 --> 00:01:46,390
This indicator basically helps to identify
whether the market is choppy (meaning consolidating

22
00:01:46,390 --> 00:01:49,380
or trading sideways) or is trending.

23
00:01:49,380 --> 00:01:55,010
Unlike many other indicators, the Choppiness
Index is a directionless indicator.

24
00:01:55,010 --> 00:01:59,560
The value of Choppiness Index indicator ranges
between 0 and 100.

25
00:01:59,560 --> 00:02:06,749
A high reading in the Choppiness Index usually
happens when there is a significant consolidation

26
00:02:06,749 --> 00:02:09,950
in the price action.

27
00:02:09,950 --> 00:02:15,670
Here is how this simple indicator can help
you record better results when swing trading:

28
00:02:15,670 --> 00:02:22,550
Choppy: When the value of the indicator is
above 61.8, it means that the market is moving

29
00:02:22,550 --> 00:02:26,280
sideways, in a choppy (consolidating) manner.

30
00:02:26,280 --> 00:02:33,730
Usually, the trend continues to be sideways
as long as Choppiness index stays above 50

31
00:02:33,730 --> 00:02:34,950
line.

32
00:02:34,950 --> 00:02:37,390
Pay attention to this example.

33
00:02:37,390 --> 00:02:44,030
Look at the Choppiness index reaching high
values and also look at the price action.

34
00:02:44,030 --> 00:02:49,190
Nothing but consolidation, sideways moves
and market indecision.

35
00:02:49,190 --> 00:02:56,650
So, the closer the value is to 100, the higher
the choppiness levels.

36
00:02:56,650 --> 00:03:03,530
Trending: When the value of the indicator
is below 38.2, it means that the market is

37
00:03:03,530 --> 00:03:04,610
trending.

38
00:03:04,610 --> 00:03:11,390
Usually, the stock remains trending as long
as Choppiness index stays below the mid 50

39
00:03:11,390 --> 00:03:12,390
line.

40
00:03:12,390 --> 00:03:14,560
Let’s analyze another example.

41
00:03:14,560 --> 00:03:21,360
Observe that when the indicator shows lower
values, the market is moving nicely.

42
00:03:21,360 --> 00:03:26,980
So, the closer the value is to 0, the stronger
the market is trending.

43
00:03:26,980 --> 00:03:33,810
End of Trend: When the value of the indicator
is below 25, it could mean that the prevailing

44
00:03:33,810 --> 00:03:37,230
trend may come to an end very soon.

45
00:03:37,230 --> 00:03:39,370
Take this as a warning sign.

46
00:03:39,370 --> 00:03:45,810
This doesn’t mean that the price will reverse,
it may continue to move nicely, but you should

47
00:03:45,810 --> 00:03:52,250
take a closer look at price action and act
accordingly when potential reversals occur.

48
00:03:52,250 --> 00:03:58,301
Now, let’s see a couple of swing trading
techniques you can implement using the choppiness

49
00:03:58,301 --> 00:03:59,930
index.

50
00:03:59,930 --> 00:04:05,520
The first swing trading technique involves
buying or selling the Breakout after high

51
00:04:05,520 --> 00:04:08,100
Choppiness Index Readings.

52
00:04:08,100 --> 00:04:14,710
In swing trading, it is generally believed
that extended periods of consolidation (meaning

53
00:04:14,710 --> 00:04:20,900
sideways trading) are followed by an extended
period of trending (strong, directional movement)

54
00:04:20,900 --> 00:04:22,940
and vice versa.

55
00:04:22,940 --> 00:04:25,660
So, here is how you could trade this.

56
00:04:25,660 --> 00:04:32,720
When a stock is trending above the 61.8 level
for an extended period of time, this is a

57
00:04:32,720 --> 00:04:35,280
sign that the market is practically flat.

58
00:04:35,280 --> 00:04:43,100
A valid approach would be to wait for a fall
back below the 61.8 level to signal a trend

59
00:04:43,100 --> 00:04:44,100
inception.

60
00:04:44,100 --> 00:04:51,280
In this case, once the choppiness index fell
below that level, this coincided with a nice

61
00:04:51,280 --> 00:04:58,220
breakout, and the price rallied upwards.

62
00:04:58,220 --> 00:05:00,090
Take a look at this chart.

63
00:05:00,090 --> 00:05:03,690
We have the same pattern, but on the downside.

64
00:05:03,690 --> 00:05:09,040
Remember that the Choppiness index is non
directional, so high readings are traded the

65
00:05:09,040 --> 00:05:13,850
same for an uptrend or downtrend.

66
00:05:13,850 --> 00:05:20,810
Here the indicator breaks below the level,
after a prolonged period of choppiness, practically

67
00:05:20,810 --> 00:05:26,280
giving confirmation that the breakout was
valid.

68
00:05:26,280 --> 00:05:31,110
Another technique involving the Choppiness
index is riding the trend when the indicator

69
00:05:31,110 --> 00:05:34,020
shows values below 45.

70
00:05:34,020 --> 00:05:39,139
So, instead of using 2 levels, we focus on
just one.

71
00:05:39,139 --> 00:05:46,260
Basically, when the indicator’s line stays
below the 45 level for a long period, we look

72
00:05:46,260 --> 00:05:50,090
for swing opportunities in the direction of
the main trend.

73
00:05:50,090 --> 00:05:55,650
Don’t overcomplicate your trading, focus
on price action, support and resistance and

74
00:05:55,650 --> 00:06:00,169
maybe add a moving average for a better understanding
of the trend.

75
00:06:00,169 --> 00:06:06,840
So, in this chart, we have several buying
opportunities, when the Choppiness index is

76
00:06:06,840 --> 00:06:14,280
below 45 and the price is trading above the
moving average.

77
00:06:14,280 --> 00:06:20,400
Look how easy is to identify the trend using
this indicator.

78
00:06:20,400 --> 00:06:29,840
As long as the choppiness is at low levels,
your swing positions should be safe.

79
00:06:29,840 --> 00:06:37,450
Here are some short opportunities, as the
price is making consecutive lows and the choppiness

80
00:06:37,450 --> 00:06:40,730
index stays below 45.

81
00:06:40,730 --> 00:06:49,470
Also, the price stayed below the moving average,
confirming the downtrend.

82
00:06:49,470 --> 00:06:55,000
Remember to always have an exit plan, because
this indicator doesn’t provide the best

83
00:06:55,000 --> 00:06:58,910
exit signals.

84
00:06:58,910 --> 00:07:04,889
Another great way to swing trade with the
choppiness index is to combine it with volume.

85
00:07:04,889 --> 00:07:09,410
Where there is volume, there is likely something
to happen on the market.

86
00:07:09,410 --> 00:07:15,260
Volume is an important indicator that can
be used to confirm certain price movement.

87
00:07:15,260 --> 00:07:19,270
It is always positive to see increasing volume
when a stock is advancing.

88
00:07:19,270 --> 00:07:26,260
Likewise, it is good to see an increase in
volume during a breakout from a consolidation

89
00:07:26,260 --> 00:07:27,260
range.

90
00:07:27,260 --> 00:07:33,320
So, when we combine choppiness index with
the volume, we could have one of the strongest

91
00:07:33,320 --> 00:07:36,720
confirmation we need in order to take a trade.

92
00:07:36,720 --> 00:07:46,889
So, here we have a consolidation phase, with
sideways price action, relatively low volume

93
00:07:46,889 --> 00:07:50,310
and the high choppiness readings.

94
00:07:50,310 --> 00:07:58,830
Observe how the volume started to increase,
while the price was still in the range.

95
00:07:58,830 --> 00:08:07,550
Once the indicator’s line crossed below
the 61.8 level, the price broke the range

96
00:08:07,550 --> 00:08:08,830
moved upward.

97
00:08:08,830 --> 00:08:17,740
The volume confirmed the valid breakout, as
it increased gradually through the move.

98
00:08:17,740 --> 00:08:22,979
The same pattern here, but on the downside.

99
00:08:22,979 --> 00:08:31,090
Price action was indicating a range, low volume
which starts to increase once the price approaches

100
00:08:31,090 --> 00:08:33,880
the support line.

101
00:08:33,880 --> 00:08:37,969
The choppiness index at high levels.

102
00:08:37,969 --> 00:08:44,990
And the breakout, with the volume showing
increasing momentum.

103
00:08:44,990 --> 00:08:50,749
Remember that the Choppiness Index does not
predict future direction, it is simply a measure

104
00:08:50,749 --> 00:08:53,149
of current trend status.

105
00:08:53,149 --> 00:09:00,829
You could say that it also measures volatility,
but you cannot use it to take trades blindly.

106
00:09:00,829 --> 00:09:07,339
The Choppiness Index one of the best indicators
to evaluate the market, but price action,

107
00:09:07,339 --> 00:09:13,199
support and resistance and volume should be
your main focus.

108
00:09:13,199 --> 00:09:19,939
Analyze the market, determine the main trend,
have a defined action plan and after that

109
00:09:19,939 --> 00:09:23,800
confirm your bias with the choppiness index.

110
00:09:23,800 --> 00:09:31,180
The true strength in this indicator is best
displayed when used as a confirmation that

111
00:09:31,180 --> 00:09:35,350
a stock is starting to trend or breaking out.

